<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Democracy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=38" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> has declared <a href="/wiki/September_15" title="September 15">Sept. 15</a> as the <a href="/wiki/International_Day_of_Democracy" title="International Day of Democracy">International Day of Democracy</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-72" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-72" title=""><span>[</span>73<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Democracy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=39" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3D%2324422" class="external text" title="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3D%2324422" rel="nofollow">Demokratia, Henry George Liddell, Robert Scott, "A Greek-English Lexicon", at Perseus</a></li>
