<li id="cite_note-65"><b><a href="#cite_ref-65" title="">^</a></b> Novanglus, no. 7, 6 Mar. 1775</li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://press-pubs.uchicago.edu/founders/documents/v1ch4I.html" class="external text" title="http://press-pubs.uchicago.edu/founders/documents/v1ch4I.html" rel="nofollow">Republican Government: Introduction</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-67"><b><a href="#cite_ref-67" title="">^</a></b> Caplan, Bryan. "From Friedman to Wittman: The Transformation of Chicago Political Economy" (April 2005). <a href="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CaplanCommentApril2005.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CaplanCommentApril2005.pdf" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-68"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68" title="">^</a></b> Plato, <i>the Republic of Plato</i> (London: J.M Dent &amp; Sons LTD.; New York: E.P. Dutton &amp; Co. Inc.), 558-C.</li>
